<span class="header1">BUSINESS SALES</span>
<p>People who do well in this occupations are self-starters and can be responsible for their own schedule.  In addition, they like meeting new people.  If this describes you, consider the occupations in this field.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Insurance Agent</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/C506005.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Insurance Agent" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>An insurance agent sells and services insurance policies.  People buy insurance for their homes, cars, and even health.  It protects them from losing a lot of money if something happens to their possessions or themselves.  But choosing the right insurance can be difficult.  As an insurance agent, you would help people decide what type of insurance policy they need. You would also help them to file a claim to collect money on their policy when necessary.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Some companies insist on a Bachelor's Degree in economics or business. But many companies don't. Instead, they provide on-the-job training. A state license is required.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>An insurance agent is paid on commission. This means that he/she is paid based on the number and price of the insurance policies sold.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Travel Agent</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/1216.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Travel Agent">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>When people go on trips, they often make transportation and hotel reservations. A travel agent is important to a traveler. If you were a travel agent, you would work very closely with the public making arrangements for vacations or business trips. You might work for a hotel or an airline. A good agent must be able to work well with people and understand the needs of a traveler.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job.  You also need to know how to use a computer.  Geography and history will be important.  Many of the places that people visit are studied in these courses.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly average income of a reservation agent is $26,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Cashier</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/1142.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Cashier">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A cashier takes the money of customers who want to buy something from a store.  As a cashier, you would ring up the items the customer wanted to buy. You would handle cash, checks and credit and debit card purchases. It would be important that the amount of money in the cash drawer matched the amount on the receipts in the machine.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>If you were a cashier, you would be given on-the-job training.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>Many cashier jobs pay minimum wage. Some pay as much as $20,000 a year.</blockquote>

