<span class="header1">BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION</span>
<p>In the occupations in this field, you would make sure that others did their jobs correctly, and that the business actions ran smoothly. If you enjoy overseeing the work of others, consider the occupations in this field.  Here are three examples.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Human Resources Manager</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/1372.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Human Resource Manager">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A human resources manager helps to develop and carry out a company's "people" policies.  He/she serves as a link between employees and upper management. As a human resources manager, you might hire or fire employees.  You might also write job descriptions and train new employees.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a Bachelor's Degree for this job.  This degree should be in human resources management.  It could also be in personnel administration.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $36,000 to $114,000+.  Salary depends on experience and education.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Employee Benefits Manager</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Companies often provide their employees with benefits such as paid vacation time and health insurance. These are called employee benefits.  An employee benefits manager helps employees to understand their benefits. She/he also helps them to use these benefits to their advantage. As an employee benefits manager, you would need to be well organized. You would also need to enjoy working with people.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You would need at least a Bachelor's Degree for this job.  It is important to take courses in insurance, business management, and finance.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $36,000 to $114,000+.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Personnel Clerk</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/43328.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Personnel Clerk">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Companies keep information about each of their employees on file.  This information includes each employee's job application. It includes information about any job evaluations as well. As a personnel clerk, you would keep employee files up to date and secure. You would use a computer to do this.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job.  You need a Bachelor's Degree if you plan to stay with the company and be promoted.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The average salary is $30,000 a year.</blockquote>

