<span class="header1">BUSINESS FINANCIAL</span>
<p>People who do well in the occupations in this field enjoy working with money. They also are good organizers and can keep track of details.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Loan Officer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/C506008.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Loan Officer">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A loan officer works for a bank or lending company. As a loan officer, you help customers fill out loan applications and make sure that the information on the application is correct. You would then see if the people wanting the loan met your company's guidelines for a loan. If so, you would help to process the loan.  If not, you would help them to understand why they did not get the loan.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a Bachelor's Degree for this job.  Some banks and lending companies only hire those with a Master's Degree in business administration.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary range for a loan officer is $26,000 to $89,000 per year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Bookkeeper</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/1287.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Bookkeeper">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>All companies must keep detailed records of their cash flow and how much money they earn. As a bookkeeper, you would be responsible for keeping this information. You would have to enjoy working with numbers and be good at keeping track of details to do this job well.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job. Most companies offer on-the-job training. Courses in business math and computer science from a vocational school can help you to get a job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $19,000 to $30,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Bank Teller</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/1371.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Bank Teller">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A bank teller handles large sums of money. As a bank teller, you would help customers with their deposits and withdrawals. Banks look for people who work well with customers, have good math skills, and know the importance of keeping detailed records.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A high school diploma is needed to be a bank teller. A teller is given on-the-job training.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A bank teller earns $9,000 to $24,000.</blockquote>

